<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_farsylyvzag" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>farsylyvzag</orth></form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>farsi ævzag</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>селезенка</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>spleen</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Буквально „язык (%iyvzag%i) на боку (%ifarsyl%i)“; см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fars"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yvzag"/>. По связи с %ifars%i
        ‘бок’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
            ><lang/><w>a-vanəza</w><gloss><q>селезенка</q></gloss></mentioned>, от <mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>a-va(ra)</w><gloss><q>бок</q></gloss></mentioned> („то, что
        прикреплено к боку“).</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Literally ‘a tongue (%iyvzag%i) on the side (%ifarsyl%i)’; see <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yvzag"/>. In
        connection to %ifars%i ‘side’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><lang/><w>a-vanəza</w><gloss><q>spleen</q></gloss></mentioned>, from <mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>a-va(ra)</w><gloss><q>side</q></gloss></mentioned> (‘thing that
        is attached to the side’).</etym>
</entry>
